Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.87,0:01:53.59,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fad(450,390)\shad3\be2\bord1\pos(358,370)}Noboru Yamaguchi (16) (Comedy nut)\NRadio name: ''Ajishio Taro''
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.12,0:01:49.50,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,How stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.50,0:01:53.63,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\pos(358,478)}It's a crime that someone gets paid\Nto make such a stupid show.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.42,0:01:59.18,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Moreover, to make the matter worse, the ratings\Ntend to be high when the show is so worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.76,0:02:02.01,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But let me say one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.01,0:02:06.56,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Even if the numbers are good,\Nit's trash unless I approve!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.27,0:02:10.27,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Pootan is always great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.07,0:02:14.44,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The current TV shows are already belly-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.07,0:02:13.82,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB7D2DC&\pos(358,435)}Ishikawa got knocked out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.44,0:02:16.07,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB7D2DC&\pos(358,405)}He took a tremendous kick to his jaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.44,0:02:18.03,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,As I thought, the only option is for me to\Nbecome a comedian and correct this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.07,0:02:18.03,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB7D2DC&\pos(358,405)}I wonder if Yamaguchi doesn't like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.74,0:02:20.03,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I don't mind doing it on my own,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.03,0:02:23.66,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,but I worry if the public\Ncan follow my high-level comedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.12,0:02:27.83,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,lf only I had a powerful partner who\Ncould handle my sense of humor...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.29,0:02:31.63,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,In that case, there's only one man\Nwho could become that partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:34.80,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\fnJust The Way You Are\pos(205.057,152)\frz13.5\frx20\fs38\fry325\c&HB4B2BE&\3c&H565E77&\bord4\be4}Open
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:34.80,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\fnDupree\fs24\pos(453.165,279)\frz348.5\frx13\fry30\bord0\c&H443128&\blur0.5}Southern
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:34.80,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\shad0\fnDupree\fs24\pos(461.095,310)\frz349\frx13\fry30\bord0\c&H443128&\blur0.5}Wind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.46,0:02:35.51,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hasn't Takenouchi lost some weight lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.84,0:02:38.26,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\an1\fad(420,0)\bord1\be2\pos(112.158,365)}Takashi Kamiyama (16)\NRadio name: "Honey Boy"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.51,0:02:38.26,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he might have thrown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.30,0:02:41.30,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fad(530,0)\bord1\be2\shad3\pos(470.158,395)}Shinjiro Hayashida (16)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.67,0:02:42.01,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\pos(358,477)}By the way, there's one thing\Nthat has been bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.01,0:02:45.64,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I feel like someone's been\Nfollowing us around lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:47.89,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Really? Aren't you imagining things?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.89,0:02:51.81,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Now, the question is what to do from here.\NHow do I approach him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.52,0:02:54.48,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If a stranger abruptly says...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.15,0:02:57.03,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Do you want to form a comedy duo with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.03,0:02:57.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.78,0:03:00.45,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It would naturally cause\NHoney Boy to shy away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.11,0:03:05.62,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I could just tell him that I am\N"postcard artisan, Ajishio Taro."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.83,0:03:09.12,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But he's ranked higher than\NI am in late-night radio shows,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:13.00,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,so there's a chance that he'll take\N the lead when we form a duo later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.00,0:03:16.09,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's not a good idea to let him\Nknow who I am right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.88,0:03:21.76,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,A while back, agencies would assign\N the partner without asking when a duo was formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:25.22,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But these days there are many cases\Nwhere the partners are classmates
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.22,0:03:27.81,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,from middle school or high school, or they\Nwere in the same theatrical company.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.56,0:03:31.89,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But we aren't classmates,\Nnor do we even go to the same school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.89,0:03:34.81,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Moreover, our schools have\Nan extremely hostile relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.57,0:03:37.82,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.82,0:03:41.07,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's dramatic when two people\Nwith no connection meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.57,0:03:43.91,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It may become a legend\Nafter we become popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.91,0:03:53.17,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fad(550,0)\bord0.8\be2\pos(358,395)}Having a head trip
